vocabulary.example: The city center was densely populated with skyscrapers.

vocabulary.definition: to be successful or fortunate, especially in financial terms
vocabulary.example: The company began to prosper after implementing new marketing strategies.

vocabulary.definition: a distant military station or a remote settlement
vocabulary.example: The soldiers were stationed at the outpost for months at a time.

vocabulary.definition: a small, crudely built shack or dwelling
vocabulary.example: Families lived in shanty houses made of scrap materials.

vocabulary.definition: well known for some bad quality or deed
vocabulary.example: The criminal was infamous for his daring bank heists.

vocabulary.definition: relating to or denoting an imagined state or society where there is great suffering or injustice
vocabulary.example: The novel depicted a dystopian future where society was controlled by a totalitarian regime.
